<h2 style="text-align: center">WATER TESTING</h2>

<p>Water quality is defined by analyzing it in terms of its: - 
<p style="margin-left: 150px;">1. <b>Chemical content</b>: - Hardness (Ca + Mg), metals (Fe, etc), nutrients (N and P), Cl, Na, organic compounds, etc..
<br>2. <b>Physical content</b>: - Turbidity, color, odor, etc.
<br>3. <b>Biological content</b>: - Fecal coliform, total coliform, viruses.

\image image1
<br>Fig. 1. Water Testing
<p style="text-align: right">(http://www.iaslabs.com/eshop_product/water-test/)

